ociallyminded business ventures with offices throughout europe asia and the united states contributing to the global society is important to us our funding guidelines are aligned with our business and community needs environment we are committed to promoting sustainable and safe communities for our employees clients and neighbors to help meet global and local environmental needs to that end we are dedicated to being environmentally responsible within each of our offices and within the communities in which we do business we approach conserving natural resources and finding alternative uses for recyclable materials with the same vigor we approach finding innovative solutions to help our clients grow their businesses as such our recycling program is implemented companywide houlihan lokey promotes the responsible use of energy throughout our business by encouraging carpooling and is proactive about protecting and preserving our natural environment through our support of various organizations education initiative further expanding on our longterm goal to advance our clients’ vision through expert advice and personalized service we are committed to preparing the next generation to help meet tomorrow’s business needs our education initiative is an integral part of who we are and what we do houlihan lokey helps children by strengthening the foundation of their education  give a day to charity houlihan lokey strives for community collaboration and partnership through our give a day to charity program we believe that investing in the future starts by fortifying local bonds and promoting understanding employees are encouraged to combine their personal efforts by organizing team volunteering events for a charity of their choice social contributions houlihan lokey promotes its aim of social responsibility through multifaceted involvement making charitable contributions in honor of clients and through charitable endeavors supported by our employees as an embodiment of this commitment we sponsor various causes and events some of the organizations to which we contribute include makeawish foundation national center for children  families the leukemia  lymphoma society covenant house behind the book second harvest food bank youth inc brooklyn arts exchange unicef human rights watch horizons for youth contribution guidelines houlihan lokey has an established process for accepting inquiries and proposals for contribution funding or charitable activities we review requests on a casebycase basis   click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more click herefor more  alternative asset valuation symposium view all events wednesday july  doddfrank’s new clo risk retention regulations – and the valuation implications for clo refinancings jonathan sloan speaks with creditflux wednesday july  ‘one of the world’s leading independent investment banks’ – the banker highlights houlihan lokey’s growth balanced business model and partnership culture in its monthly ‘agenda’ thursday july  houlihan lokey announces release date for first quarter results for fiscal year  view all news this page is not available for selected language you will be redirected to home page you are about to leave houlihan lokeys website the link below leads to a website that is not owned by houlihan lokey continue to the external website or close this window to remain on hlcom our services  houlihan lokey this website requires javascript please enable javascript in your browser and refresh the page home our servicesour services our services delivering insight and expertise to help advance your vision we guide clients through the complex financial and strategic challenges that they 